//             "lexical": "{\"root\":{\"children\":[{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"I've been a fellow of \",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Inovus Labs\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"link\",\"version\":1,\"rel\":null,\"target\":null,\"title\":null,\"url\":\"https://inovuslabs.org/\"},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\" for more than a half-dozen years. Since the very beginning, I was really fond of tinkering with the IoT components and electronics circuitry available at the mini IoT lab up there. The journey become much more interesting when more hands started pouring in. Building a smart access door for Inovus Labs has been on our collective bucket list for quite some time.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"This project is a joint venture with my Inovus fellow Mr. \",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":1,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Nikhil T Das\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"link\",\"version\":1,\"rel\":null,\"target\":null,\"title\":null,\"url\":\"https://blog.inovuslabs.org/author/nikhil/\"},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\". We express our heartfelt gratitude to the entire Inovus Execom (especially \",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Badhusha Shaji\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"link\",\"version\":1,\"rel\":\"noreferrer\",\"target\":null,\"title\":null,\"url\":\"https://blog.inovuslabs.org/author/badhusha\"},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\" & \",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Abhishek V Gopal\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"link\",\"version\":1,\"rel\":\"noreferrer\",\"target\":null,\"title\":null,\"url\":\"https://blog.inovuslabs.org/author/abhishek\"},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\") for all the support.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"quote\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Conceptualizing the Smart Door\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"heading\",\"version\":1,\"tag\":\"h3\"},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Before diving into the core technicalities, the team brainstormed to outline the system's functionalities and components. We envisioned a door access system that would enable authorized personnel to enter via RFID cards while ensuring smooth and automated closure, even when the door is barely shut. Integrating Firebase and Discord added crucial security and monitoring features to keep track of all access events.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Components Used\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"heading\",\"version\":1,\"tag\":\"h3\"},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"The following list of components was used for building the so-proposed RFID-based smart door system. All hardware components required for this project build are available online and associated purchase links are attached below.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"toggle\",\"version\":1,\"heading\":\"<span style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">Hardware R</span><b><strong style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">equirements</strong></b>\",\"content\":\"<ul><li value=\\\"1\\\"><a href=\\\"https://robu.in/product/esp-wroom-32-esp32-wifi-bt-ble-mcu-module/\\\"><u><b><strong class=\\\"underline\\\" style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">ESP32 Development Board</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">The ESP32 was chosen for its versatility, built-in WiFi capabilities, and adequate GPIO pins for interfacing with other components.</span></li><li value=\\\"2\\\"><a href=\\\"https://robu.in/product/mifare-rfid-readerwriter-13-56mhz-rc522-spi-s50-fudan-card-and-keychain/\\\"><u><b><strong class=\\\"underline\\\" style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">RFID Reader</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">A reliable RFID reader module was selected to interact with RFID cards and grant access to authorized personnel.</span></li><li value=\\\"3\\\"><a href=\\\"https://robu.in/product/mc-38-wired-door-window-sensor-magnetic-switch-home-alarm-system/\\\"><u><b><strong class=\\\"underline\\\" style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">Magnetic Switch</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">The magnetic switch served as the trigger for the auto-close mechanism. The system would initiate the auto-close process when the door was left ajar.</span></li><li value=\\\"4\\\"><a href=\\\"https://robu.in/product/orange-100pcs-5-colors-f3mm-led-kit/\\\"><u><b><strong class=\\\"underline\\\" style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">LED Indicators</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">LEDs were integrated to indicate WiFi connection status and access approval.</span></li><li value=\\\"5\\\"><a href=\\\"https://robu.in/product/5v-active-electromagnetic-buzzer-pack-of-5/\\\"><u><b><strong class=\\\"underline\\\" style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">Buzzer</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">To provide audible feedback during various events, such as successful access or an invalid RFID tag.</span></li><li value=\\\"6\\\"><a href=\\\"https://robu.in/product/1240-12v-dc-0-6a-7-5w-solenoid-for-electric-door-lock/\\\"><u><b><strong class=\\\"underline\\\" style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">12v Solenoid Lock</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">A secure lock actuated by an electric current, grants access to authorized personnel.</span></li><li value=\\\"7\\\"><a href=\\\"https://robu.in/product/1-channel-isolated-5v-relay-module-opto-coupler-for-arduino-pic-avr-dsp-arm/\\\"><u><b><strong class=\\\"underline\\\" style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">Single Relay Module</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">To control the 12v Solenoid Lock with the ESP32, the lock requires a higher current than the microcontroller can handle directly.</span></li><li value=\\\"8\\\"><a href=\\\"https://robu.in/product/jhd-20x4-character-lcd-display-with-blue-backlight/\\\"><u><b><strong class=\\\"underline\\\" style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">JHD204A LCD Display</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">An LCD screen displays status information and messages for users&nbsp;</span><i><em class=\\\"italic\\\" style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">(optional)</em></i><span style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">.</span></li></ul>\"},{\"type\":\"toggle\",\"version\":1,\"heading\":\"<span style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">Software Requirements</span>\",\"content\":\"<ul><li value=\\\"1\\\"><a href=\\\"https://firebase.google.com/docs/database\\\"><u><b><strong class=\\\"underline\\\" style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">Firebase Realtime Database</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">Firebase was adopted to store logs of all access events, ensuring easy retrieval and monitoring of activities.</span></li><li value=\\\"2\\\"><a href=\\\"https://support.discord.com/hc/en-us/articles/228383668-Intro-to-Webhooks\\\"><u><b><strong class=\\\"underline\\\" style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">Discord Webhooks</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\\\"white-space: pre-wrap;\\\">Webhooks were employed to send real-time alert messages to a dedicated Discord channel in the event of unauthorized access attempts or system malfunctions.</span></li></ul>\"},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Circuit Diagram\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"heading\",\"version\":1,\"tag\":\"h3\"},{\"type\":\"image\",\"version\":1,\"src\":\"https://blog.inovuslabs.org/content/images/2023/10/image-9.png\",\"width\":1213,\"height\":855,\"title\":\"\",\"alt\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"cardWidth\":\"regular\",\"href\":\"\"},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Code Explanation\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"heading\",\"version\":1,\"tag\":\"h3\"},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"The system only uses 6 libraries to handle all its complex tasks. The \",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":16,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"WiFi.h\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\" library enables us to establish a network connection over the available WiFi network.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"codeblock\",\"version\":1,\"code\":\"void connect_WiFi() {\\n  WiFi.mode(WIFI_STA);\\n  WiFi.begin(ssid, password);\\n  Serial.print(\\\"Connecting to WiFi ...\\\");\\n  while (WiFi.status() != WL_CONNECTED) {\\n    Serial.print('.');\\n    delay(1000);\\n  }\\n  Serial.println(WiFi.localIP());\\n}\",\"language\":\"cpp\",\"caption\":\"\"},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"The \",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":16,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"MFRC522.h\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\" library is used to read the RFID Cards / Tags. The \",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":16,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"SPI.h\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\" library allows you to communicate with SPI (Serial Peripheral Interface) devices, with the ESP32 Board as the controller device.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"codeblock\",\"version\":1,\"code\":\"void connect_MFRC() {\\n  SPI.begin();\\n  mfrc522.PCD_Init();\\n  Serial.println(\\\"\\\\nReady to read RFID tags...\\\");\\n}\",\"language\":\"cpp\",\"caption\":\"\"},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"And here's the most overkill part of the project build. The project sends out an alert for every legit activity happening around this, such as Authorized & Unauthorized Door Access and Autoclose trigger. The \",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":16,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"HTTPClient.h\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\" library helps us to easily make HTTP - \",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":1,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"GET\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\", \",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":1,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"POST\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\", and \",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":1,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"PUT \",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"requests to a web server.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"codeblock\",\"version\":1,\"code\":\"void sendDiscordWebhook() {\\n  HTTPClient http;\\n  http.begin(webhook_url);\\n  http.addHeader(\\\"Content-Type\\\", \\\"application/json\\\");\\n\\n  if(autoLock == true ) {\\n    \\n    // define the json to notify the trigger of an autoclose\\n    \\n  } else {  \\n\\n    if(owner != \\\"\\\") {\\n  \\n      // json to notify the trigger for a successful door opening\\n    \\n    } else {\\n    \\n      // // json to notify the trigger for an unsuccessful door opening\\n      \\n    }\\n  }\\n  Serial.println(json);\\n  \\n  int http_code = http.POST(json);\\n  if (http_code == 204) {\\n    Serial.println(\\\"Discord Webhook Sent...\\\");\\n  } else {\\n    Serial.println(\\\"Error sending webhook...\\\");\\n  }\\n}\",\"language\":\"cpp\",\"caption\":\"\"},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"The status of the WiFi connection is checked every 30 seconds and in case of any issues, it'll disconnect and attempt to reconnect on its own.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"codeblock\",\"version\":1,\"code\":\"unsigned long previousMillis = 0;\\nunsigned long interval = 30000;\\n\\nunsigned long currentMillis = millis();\\n  if ((WiFi.status() != WL_CONNECTED) && (currentMillis - previousMillis >=interval)) {\\n    Serial.println(\\\"Reconnecting to WiFi...\\\");\\n    WiFi.disconnect();\\n    WiFi.reconnect();\\n    previousMillis = currentMillis;\\n  }\",\"language\":\"cpp\",\"caption\":\"\"},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Every door activity is logged onto a Firebase Real-time Database. The \",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":16,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"time.h\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\" library helps us to handle date & time-related activities, just like \",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":16,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Date()\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\" in JavaScript. The \",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":16,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Firebase_ESP_Client\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\" library supports RTDB, Cloud Firestore, Google Cloud Storage, Cloud Messaging, and other Cloud Functions for Firebase.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Results\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"heading\",\"version\":1,\"tag\":\"h3\"},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"A simple dashboard was built using vanilla JavaScript to showcase the current status of the door and the so collected activity history.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Hereby adding the live dashboard demo link.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"linebreak\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":2,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"(Sorry that we couldn't care for its device responsiveness)\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\".\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"linebreak\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":9,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"https://door.dashboard.inovuslabs.org/\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"link\",\"version\":1,\"rel\":null,\"target\":null,\"title\":null,\"url\":\"https://door.dashboard.inovuslabs.org/\"}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"image\",\"version\":1,\"src\":\"https://blog.inovuslabs.org/content/images/2023/10/image-8.png\",\"width\":1365,\"height\":768,\"title\":\"\",\"alt\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"cardWidth\":\"regular\",\"href\":\"\"},{\"children\":[],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"root\",\"version\":1}}",
//             "html": "<p>I've been a fellow of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://inovuslabs.org/\">Inovus Labs</a>&nbsp;for more than a half-dozen years. Since the very beginning, I was really fond of tinkering with the IoT components and electronics circuitry available at the mini IoT lab up there. The journey become much more interesting when more hands started pouring in. Building a smart access door for Inovus Labs has been on our collective bucket list for quite some time.</p><blockquote>This project is a joint venture with my Inovus fellow Mr.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://blog.inovuslabs.org/author/nikhil/\"><strong>Nikhil T Das</strong></a>. We express our heartfelt gratitude to the entire Inovus Execom (especially <a href=\"https://blog.inovuslabs.org/author/badhusha\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Badhusha Shaji</a> &amp; <a href=\"https://blog.inovuslabs.org/author/abhishek\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Abhishek V Gopal</a>) for all the support.</blockquote><h3 id=\"conceptualizing-the-smart-door\">Conceptualizing the Smart Door</h3><p>Before diving into the core technicalities, the team brainstormed to outline the system's functionalities and components. We envisioned a door access system that would enable authorized personnel to enter via RFID cards while ensuring smooth and automated closure, even when the door is barely shut. Integrating Firebase and Discord added crucial security and monitoring features to keep track of all access events.</p><h3 id=\"components-used\">Components Used</h3><p>The following list of components was used for building the so-proposed RFID-based smart door system. All hardware components required for this project build are available online and associated purchase links are attached below.</p><div class=\"kg-card kg-toggle-card\" data-kg-toggle-state=\"close\">\n            <div class=\"kg-toggle-heading\">\n                <h4 class=\"kg-toggle-heading-text\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">Hardware R</span><b><strong style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">equirements</strong></b></h4>\n                <button class=\"kg-toggle-card-icon\">\n                    <svg id=\"Regular\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\">\n                        <path class=\"cls-1\" d=\"M23.25,7.311,12.53,18.03a.749.749,0,0,1-1.06,0L.75,7.311\"></path>\n                    </svg>\n                </button>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"kg-toggle-content\"><ul><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"https://robu.in/product/esp-wroom-32-esp32-wifi-bt-ble-mcu-module/\"><u><b><strong class=\"underline\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">ESP32 Development Board</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">The ESP32 was chosen for its versatility, built-in WiFi capabilities, and adequate GPIO pins for interfacing with other components.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"https://robu.in/product/mifare-rfid-readerwriter-13-56mhz-rc522-spi-s50-fudan-card-and-keychain/\"><u><b><strong class=\"underline\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">RFID Reader</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">A reliable RFID reader module was selected to interact with RFID cards and grant access to authorized personnel.</span></li><li value=\"3\"><a href=\"https://robu.in/product/mc-38-wired-door-window-sensor-magnetic-switch-home-alarm-system/\"><u><b><strong class=\"underline\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">Magnetic Switch</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">The magnetic switch served as the trigger for the auto-close mechanism. The system would initiate the auto-close process when the door was left ajar.</span></li><li value=\"4\"><a href=\"https://robu.in/product/orange-100pcs-5-colors-f3mm-led-kit/\"><u><b><strong class=\"underline\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">LED Indicators</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">LEDs were integrated to indicate WiFi connection status and access approval.</span></li><li value=\"5\"><a href=\"https://robu.in/product/5v-active-electromagnetic-buzzer-pack-of-5/\"><u><b><strong class=\"underline\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">Buzzer</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">To provide audible feedback during various events, such as successful access or an invalid RFID tag.</span></li><li value=\"6\"><a href=\"https://robu.in/product/1240-12v-dc-0-6a-7-5w-solenoid-for-electric-door-lock/\"><u><b><strong class=\"underline\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">12v Solenoid Lock</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">A secure lock actuated by an electric current, grants access to authorized personnel.</span></li><li value=\"7\"><a href=\"https://robu.in/product/1-channel-isolated-5v-relay-module-opto-coupler-for-arduino-pic-avr-dsp-arm/\"><u><b><strong class=\"underline\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">Single Relay Module</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">To control the 12v Solenoid Lock with the ESP32, the lock requires a higher current than the microcontroller can handle directly.</span></li><li value=\"8\"><a href=\"https://robu.in/product/jhd-20x4-character-lcd-display-with-blue-backlight/\"><u><b><strong class=\"underline\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">JHD204A LCD Display</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">An LCD screen displays status information and messages for users&nbsp;</span><i><em class=\"italic\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">(optional)</em></i><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">.</span></li></ul></div>\n        </div><div class=\"kg-card kg-toggle-card\" data-kg-toggle-state=\"close\">\n            <div class=\"kg-toggle-heading\">\n                <h4 class=\"kg-toggle-heading-text\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">Software Requirements</span></h4>\n                <button class=\"kg-toggle-card-icon\">\n                    <svg id=\"Regular\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\">\n                        <path class=\"cls-1\" d=\"M23.25,7.311,12.53,18.03a.749.749,0,0,1-1.06,0L.75,7.311\"></path>\n                    </svg>\n                </button>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"kg-toggle-content\"><ul><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"https://firebase.google.com/docs/database\"><u><b><strong class=\"underline\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">Firebase Realtime Database</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">Firebase was adopted to store logs of all access events, ensuring easy retrieval and monitoring of activities.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"https://support.discord.com/hc/en-us/articles/228383668-Intro-to-Webhooks\"><u><b><strong class=\"underline\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">Discord Webhooks</strong></b></u></a><br><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">Webhooks were employed to send real-time alert messages to a dedicated Discord channel in the event of unauthorized access attempts or system malfunctions.</span></li></ul></div>\n        </div><h3 id=\"circuit-diagram\">Circuit Diagram</h3><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://blog.inovuslabs.org/content/images/2023/10/image-9.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1213\" height=\"855\" srcset=\"https://blog.inovuslabs.org/content/images/size/w600/2023/10/image-9.png 600w, https://blog.inovuslabs.org/content/images/size/w1000/2023/10/image-9.png 1000w, https://blog.inovuslabs.org/content/images/2023/10/image-9.png 1213w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><h3 id=\"code-explanation\">Code Explanation</h3><p>The system only uses 6 libraries to handle all its complex tasks. The&nbsp;<code>WiFi.h</code>&nbsp;library enables us to establish a network connection over the available WiFi network.</p><pre><code class=\"language-cpp\">void connect_WiFi() {\n  WiFi.mode(WIFI_STA);\n  WiFi.begin(ssid, password);\n  Serial.print(\"Connecting to WiFi ...\");\n  while (WiFi.status() != WL_CONNECTED) {\n    Serial.print('.');\n    delay(1000);\n  }\n  Serial.println(WiFi.localIP());\n}</code></pre><p>The&nbsp;<code>MFRC522.h</code>&nbsp;library is used to read the RFID Cards / Tags. The&nbsp;<code>SPI.h</code>&nbsp;library allows you to communicate with SPI (Serial Peripheral Interface) devices, with the ESP32 Board as the controller device.</p><pre><code class=\"language-cpp\">void connect_MFRC() {\n  SPI.begin();\n  mfrc522.PCD_Init();\n  Serial.println(\"\\nReady to read RFID tags...\");\n}</code></pre><p>And here's the most overkill part of the project build. The project sends out an alert for every legit activity happening around this, such as Authorized &amp; Unauthorized Door Access and Autoclose trigger. The&nbsp;<code>HTTPClient.h</code>&nbsp;library helps us to easily make HTTP -&nbsp;<strong>GET</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>POST</strong>, and&nbsp;<strong>PUT&nbsp;</strong>requests to a web server.</p><pre><code class=\"language-cpp\">void sendDiscordWebhook() {\n  HTTPClient http;\n  http.begin(webhook_url);\n  http.addHeader(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\");\n\n  if(autoLock == true ) {\n    \n    // define the json to notify the trigger of an autoclose\n    \n  } else {  \n\n    if(owner != \"\") {\n  \n      // json to notify the trigger for a successful door opening\n    \n    } else {\n    \n      // // json to notify the trigger for an unsuccessful door opening\n      \n    }\n  }\n  Serial.println(json);\n  \n  int http_code = http.POST(json);\n  if (http_code == 204) {\n    Serial.println(\"Discord Webhook Sent...\");\n  } else {\n    Serial.println(\"Error sending webhook...\");\n  }\n}</code></pre><p>The status of the WiFi connection is checked every 30 seconds and in case of any issues, it'll disconnect and attempt to reconnect on its own.</p><pre><code class=\"language-cpp\">unsigned long previousMillis = 0;\nunsigned long interval = 30000;\n\nunsigned long currentMillis = millis();\n  if ((WiFi.status() != WL_CONNECTED) &amp;&amp; (currentMillis - previousMillis &gt;=interval)) {\n    Serial.println(\"Reconnecting to WiFi...\");\n    WiFi.disconnect();\n    WiFi.reconnect();\n    previousMillis = currentMillis;\n  }</code></pre><p>Every door activity is logged onto a Firebase Real-time Database. The&nbsp;<code>time.h</code>&nbsp;library helps us to handle date &amp; time-related activities, just like&nbsp;<code>Date()</code>&nbsp;in JavaScript. The&nbsp;<code>Firebase_ESP_Client</code>&nbsp;library supports RTDB, Cloud Firestore, Google Cloud Storage, Cloud Messaging, and other Cloud Functions for Firebase.</p><h3 id=\"results\">Results</h3><p>A simple dashboard was built using vanilla JavaScript to showcase the current status of the door and the so collected activity history.</p><p>Hereby adding the live dashboard demo link.<br><em>(Sorry that we couldn't care for its device responsiveness)</em>.<br><a href=\"https://door.dashboard.inovuslabs.org/\"><strong><u>https://door.dashboard.inovuslabs.org/</u></strong></a></p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://blog.inovuslabs.org/content/images/2023/10/image-8.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1365\" height=\"768\" srcset=\"https://blog.inovuslabs.org/content/images/size/w600/2023/10/image-8.png 600w, https://blog.inovuslabs.org/content/images/size/w1000/2023/10/image-8.png 1000w, https://blog.inovuslabs.org/content/images/2023/10/image-8.png 1365w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure>",
