//             "lexical": "{\"root\":{\"children\":[{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"In the software industry, good design is essential for creating software that is user-friendly, intuitive, and effective. It can make the difference between a successful software product and one that fails to gain traction in the market. As such, design has a significant presence in the software industry and is a key factor in the success of software products.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Design plays a crucial role in creating user-friendly and visually appealing software products. It is the process of creating a plan or blueprint for the construction of an object or system. It involves considering the purpose, function, aesthetics, and user experience of the object or system being designed.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"What is UI/UX ?\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"heading\",\"version\":1,\"tag\":\"h3\"},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"UI (User Interface) and UX (User Experience) are two essential elements of software design that are often used interchangeably but have distinct roles. UI refers to the visual design elements of software, including layout, typography, and color scheme. UX, on the other hand, encompasses the overall user experience, from the user's initial impression of the software to their experience using it to achieve their goals.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":1,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"How UI and UX are not the same\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"image\",\"version\":1,\"src\":\"https://blog.inovuslabs.org/content/images/2023/10/image--5-.png\",\"width\":324,\"height\":540,\"title\":\"\",\"alt\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"cardWidth\":\"regular\",\"href\":\"\"},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"UI (User Interface) and UX (User Experience) are two different aspects of software design that work together to create a successful software product.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"UI design is primarily concerned with the visual elements of the software, such as the layout, color scheme, typography, and other graphical elements. The goal of UI design is to create an aesthetically pleasing and intuitive interface that users find easy to navigate.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"UX design, on the other hand, is concerned with the overall experience that a user has when interacting with the software. UX designers focus on understanding the user's needs and behaviors, designing the software in a way that meets those needs, and ensuring that the user experience is seamless and enjoyable.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":1,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Why is it hard for tech industries to choose UI and UX Designers\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"image\",\"version\":1,\"src\":\"https://blog.inovuslabs.org/content/images/2023/10/image-1.png\",\"width\":493,\"height\":751,\"title\":\"\",\"alt\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"cardWidth\":\"regular\",\"href\":\"\"},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Without UI or UX designers, software products would likely suffer from a lack of user-centered design.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"When UI designers are absent, software products might be poorly designed visually, making them difficult to use, confusing, or unappealing to users. This could result in decreased user satisfaction, reduced user engagement, and ultimately, lower adoption and revenue for the software product.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"When UX designers are absent, software products might not be designed with the user's needs and behaviors in mind, making them difficult to use, frustrating, or irrelevant to the user's goals. This could lead to increased user churn, lower retention rates, and ultimately, decreased revenue for the software product.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":1,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Why UI/UX should be considered as a career option\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"image\",\"version\":1,\"src\":\"https://blog.inovuslabs.org/content/images/2023/10/meme.jpg\",\"width\":522,\"height\":550,\"title\":\"\",\"alt\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"cardWidth\":\"regular\",\"href\":\"\"},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Even though this field is exhausting, UI and UX design are rapidly growing fields in the technology industry, and they offer several compelling reasons why they should be considered as a career option:\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"High demand: As the importance of user-centered design continues to grow, the demand for UI/UX designers is increasing. According to recent job market data, UI/UX design jobs are in high demand and are projected to grow significantly in the coming years.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"listitem\",\"version\":1,\"value\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Competitive pay: According to recent job market data, the average salary of a UI designer in India is around INR 6,00,000 to INR 8,00,000 per annum and UX designer is around INR 6,00,000 to INR 9,00,000 per annum.. However, experienced and skilled designers with a good portfolio can earn significantly higher salaries.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"listitem\",\"version\":1,\"value\":2},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Creativity and problem-solving: UI/UX design requires a unique blend of creativity and problem-solving skills, which can make for a stimulating and rewarding career.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"listitem\",\"version\":1,\"value\":3},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Positive impact: UI/UX designers have the opportunity to make a positive impact on users by creating intuitive, easy-to-use interfaces that enhance the user experience.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"listitem\",\"version\":1,\"value\":4},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Career growth: UI/UX design offers opportunities for career growth and advancement, including roles such as UX researcher, UX strategist, design director, and more.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"listitem\",\"version\":1,\"value\":5}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"list\",\"version\":1,\"listType\":\"bullet\",\"start\":1,\"tag\":\"ul\"},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"In conclusion, User Interface and Experience designs are crucial elements of digital product development that focus on creating engaging and user-friendly interfaces that enhance the overall user experience. These fields offer compelling career options, with high demand, competitive salaries, and opportunities for creativity and problem-solving. With the rapid growth of the technology industry, UI/UX design is expected to continue to be an in-demand career field, offering opportunities for personal and professional growth and impact.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"root\",\"version\":1}}",
//             "html": "<p>In the software industry, good design is essential for creating software that is user-friendly, intuitive, and effective. It can make the difference between a successful software product and one that fails to gain traction in the market. As such, design has a significant presence in the software industry and is a key factor in the success of software products.</p><p>Design plays a crucial role in creating user-friendly and visually appealing software products. It is the process of creating a plan or blueprint for the construction of an object or system. It involves considering the purpose, function, aesthetics, and user experience of the object or system being designed.</p><h3 id=\"what-is-uiux\">What is UI/UX ?</h3><p>UI (User Interface) and UX (User Experience) are two essential elements of software design that are often used interchangeably but have distinct roles. UI refers to the visual design elements of software, including layout, typography, and color scheme. UX, on the other hand, encompasses the overall user experience, from the user's initial impression of the software to their experience using it to achieve their goals.</p><p><strong>How UI and UX are not the same</strong></p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://blog.inovuslabs.org/content/images/2023/10/image--5-.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"324\" height=\"540\"></figure><p>UI (User Interface) and UX (User Experience) are two different aspects of software design that work together to create a successful software product.</p><p>UI design is primarily concerned with the visual elements of the software, such as the layout, color scheme, typography, and other graphical elements. The goal of UI design is to create an aesthetically pleasing and intuitive interface that users find easy to navigate.</p><p>UX design, on the other hand, is concerned with the overall experience that a user has when interacting with the software. UX designers focus on understanding the user's needs and behaviors, designing the software in a way that meets those needs, and ensuring that the user experience is seamless and enjoyable.</p><p><strong>Why is it hard for tech industries to choose UI and UX Designers</strong></p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://blog.inovuslabs.org/content/images/2023/10/image-1.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"493\" height=\"751\"></figure><p>Without UI or UX designers, software products would likely suffer from a lack of user-centered design.</p><p>When UI designers are absent, software products might be poorly designed visually, making them difficult to use, confusing, or unappealing to users. This could result in decreased user satisfaction, reduced user engagement, and ultimately, lower adoption and revenue for the software product.</p><p>When UX designers are absent, software products might not be designed with the user's needs and behaviors in mind, making them difficult to use, frustrating, or irrelevant to the user's goals. This could lead to increased user churn, lower retention rates, and ultimately, decreased revenue for the software product.</p><p><strong>Why UI/UX should be considered as a career option</strong></p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://blog.inovuslabs.org/content/images/2023/10/meme.jpg\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"522\" height=\"550\"></figure><p>Even though this field is exhausting, UI and UX design are rapidly growing fields in the technology industry, and they offer several compelling reasons why they should be considered as a career option:</p><ul><li>High demand: As the importance of user-centered design continues to grow, the demand for UI/UX designers is increasing. According to recent job market data, UI/UX design jobs are in high demand and are projected to grow significantly in the coming years.</li><li>Competitive pay: According to recent job market data, the average salary of a UI designer in India is around INR 6,00,000 to INR 8,00,000 per annum and UX designer is around INR 6,00,000 to INR 9,00,000 per annum.. However, experienced and skilled designers with a good portfolio can earn significantly higher salaries.</li><li>Creativity and problem-solving: UI/UX design requires a unique blend of creativity and problem-solving skills, which can make for a stimulating and rewarding career.</li><li>Positive impact: UI/UX designers have the opportunity to make a positive impact on users by creating intuitive, easy-to-use interfaces that enhance the user experience.</li><li>Career growth: UI/UX design offers opportunities for career growth and advancement, including roles such as UX researcher, UX strategist, design director, and more.</li></ul><p>In conclusion, User Interface and Experience designs are crucial elements of digital product development that focus on creating engaging and user-friendly interfaces that enhance the overall user experience. These fields offer compelling career options, with high demand, competitive salaries, and opportunities for creativity and problem-solving. With the rapid growth of the technology industry, UI/UX design is expected to continue to be an in-demand career field, offering opportunities for personal and professional growth and impact.</p>",
