//             "lexical": "{\"root\":{\"children\":[{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Imagine regular dreams as surprise parties your brain throws without telling you the plan. It's like watching a TV show without a remote, where anything can happen, and you're just along for the ride. Now, lucid dreams are like getting a special pass to that party. You become the superhero, thinking, \\\"Hey, this is my dream! I can fly and order pizza!\\\" Unlike the unpredictable fun of normal dreams, lucid dreams are like being in charge of your own Netflix show. You control the story, characters, and can turn serious stuff into funny moments. It's like making deals with your brain, saying, \\\"I'd rather be in a cozy mountain cabin than climbing Everest.\\\" Lucid dreams let you be the DJ too, playing cool beats or turning a cat playing bagpipes into a conductor leading a cat orchestra. In regular dreams, it's like reading a mystery novel but accidentally jumping to the end. Lucid dreams make you both the writer and the detective, solving mysteries and maybe even finding out the butler did it with a spaghetti noodle!\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Explaining a lucid dream in a funny way is like this. But what is a lucid dream? Is there anything scary about it?\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"linebreak\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"horizontalrule\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Dreams have always been a mysterious realm, offering a glimpse into our subconscious minds. Among these dreams, there exists a fascinating phenomenon known as lucid dreaming – a state where the dreamer becomes fully aware that they are in a dream. In this blog, we'll delve into the intriguing world of lucid dreams, exploring the distinctions from regular dreams, the advantages, potential pitfalls, and the side effects of lucid dreaming, including sleep paralysis.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"horizontalrule\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":1,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Unveiling the Difference: Normal Dreams vs. Lucid Dreams\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":2,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Normal Dreams:\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\" Normal dreams unfold as we sleep, presenting vivid and sometimes fantastical experiences. In these dreams, the dreamer is immersed in the dream world without questioning its reality. The dreamer may only become aware of the dream's nature upon waking up.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":2,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Lucid Dreams:\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\" Lucid dreams, on the other hand, offer a unique level of consciousness. In this state, the dreamer realizes they are in a dream and gains varying degrees of control over the dream's narrative. This awareness transforms the dreamer from a passive observer to an active participant in the dream world.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"horizontalrule\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":1,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"The Advantages of Lucid Dreaming\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":2,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Exploration and Control:\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\" Lucid dreaming opens up the possibility to actively shape and alter the course of dreams. Dreamers can explore their own inner landscapes, facing fears, practicing real-life skills, and enjoying a heightened sense of awareness and adventure.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":2,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Creativity and Fulfillment:\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\" Lucid dreams serve as a platform for creative expression. Dreamers can engage in experiences that may not be possible in waking life, leading to a fulfilling and imaginative dream journey.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":2,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Entertainment and Personal Insight:\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\" Beyond the therapeutic aspects, lucid dreaming offers a source of entertainment and personal insight. It becomes a canvas for self-discovery, providing a space to explore the depths of one's mind.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"horizontalrule\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":1,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Potential Disadvantages to Consider\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":2,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Blurring of Dream and Reality:\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\" For some individuals, the boundary between dream and reality may blur, potentially leading to difficulties in distinguishing between the two states. It's crucial to maintain a healthy balance.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":2,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Sleep Disturbances:\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\" Excessive focus on lucid dreaming can lead to sleep disturbances or disruptions, affecting overall sleep quality. Striking a balance between lucid dreaming and restful sleep is essential.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"children\":[{\"detail\":0,\"format\":2,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\"Accessibility Challenges:\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1},{\"detail\":0,\"format\":0,\"mode\":\"normal\",\"style\":\"\",\"text\":\" Achieving lucid dreaming may not be an easily attainable skill for everyone. Despite various techniques, some individuals may find the experience elusive.\",\"type\":\"extended-text\",\"version\":1}],\"direction\":\"ltr\",\"format\":\"\",\"indent\":0,\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"version\":1},{\"type\":\"horizonta